text:

folder: Rockwell Place & Fulton Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
79-93 Rockwell Place, east side, between Fulton Street and Lafayette Avenue, showing a clearance which, if buildings were to be erected on it, will bear the above street numbers. The building seen across the shack is the Momart Theatre, which touches also on Fulton Street.

May 17, 1940

P. L. Sperr
